claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: Title page of an original article titled “Recombinant or Standard-Dose Influenza Vaccine in Adults under 65 Years of Age,” listing authors but no data or statements about vaccine production methods or mutations. The image contains only the article title and author list and does not present any information on cell- or egg-based vaccine production, mutations, or their impact on effectiveness, and thus does not support the claim. Note: Limited excerpt; no content on production methods or mutation data is visible.
